<TITLE> Bangladesh missions in US collect Tk 3.5 crore for Sidr relief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 29 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Embassy in Washington and two consulate offices at New York and Los Angeles have collected a total of Tk 3.5 crore for the aid of cyclone victims, an embassy statement said Thursday. The Bangladesh Embassy in Washington DC formed a coordination cell immediately after Cyclone Sidr and asked the Bangladeshi community in the US to donate funds for the survivors. In response, Bangladeshis and many US well-wishers have donated money to the chief adviser's relief fund maintained with the embassy in Washington. The Bangladesh Embassy and Consulates are operating the fund raising activities collaboratively. The funds will be sent to Bangladesh as early as possible. bdnews
